 has led to speculations that it undertakes seasonal short-distance migrations. Fairly widely distributed and not particularly rare, it is not considered a threatened species by the IUCN. This is a shy species which tends to keep to cover as it forages in low branches for insects and other arthropods. The female lays two white eggs in a deep cup nest in a tree or bamboo. Like most American cuckoos, it incubates the eggs itself. References External links Little Cuckoo videos on the Internet Bird Collection Little Cuckoo photo gallery Archived 2011-06-14 at the Wayback Machine VIREO Photo-High Res; Article pbase.com Photo-High Res; Article geometer–\"Best Bird Photos\"", "shortSummary": "The little cuckoo (Coccycua minuta) is a species of bird in the cuckoo family (Cuculidae) from South America and Panama. It was formerly pl…", "habitats": ["沼泽"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Coccycua_minuta_Little_Cuckoo%3B_Miranda%2C_Mato_Grosso_do_Sul%2C_Brazil.jpg/960px-Coccycua_minuta_Little_Cuckoo%3B_Miranda%2C_Mato_Grosso_do_Sul%2C_Brazil.jpg", "order": "Cuculiformes", "family": "Cuculidae", "genus": "Coccycua", "species": "Coccycua minuta", "orderCn": "鹃形目", "familyCn": "杜鹃科", "genusCn": "小棕鹃属", "speciesCn": "小棕鹃", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-cuculiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-cuculidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-coccycua", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-coccycua-minuta", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-cuculiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-cuculidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-coccycua", "species": "taxonomy-species-coccycua-minuta"}, "expandable": true, "x": -893.08, "y": -191.48, "z": 79.0}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-coccycua", "name": "小棕鹃属", "latinName": "Coccycua", "type": "taxonomy", "tax